description:
&lt;p&gt;Solent NHS Trust would like to invite enthusiastic and motivated Bank Health Visitors, to join our flexible workforce delivering The Healthy Child Programme to children and families across Southampton City.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At Solent NHS Trust, our approach to delivering services to children and families is innovative, progressive and committed to putting client care at the center of all we do. We are looking for dedicated resilient professionals who promote our HEART values and share our passion for delivering high quality care.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This post offers an excellent opportunity to work flexibly whilst delivering an effective Public Health service, you will utilise your skills to promote improved outcomes for children and families in Public Health England’s six High Impact Areas. Solent NHS is committed to developing creative ways of providing timely, effective interventions.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our Health Visitors are well supported through a positive culture of regular clinical and safeguarding supervision and one to one line management. We recognise our skilled workforce as our most valuable resource and support continual professional development, offering ongoing learning opportunities.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidates will have excellent communication skills, be flexible, adaptable and have the ability to implement new and exciting ways of working. Good organisational skills, the ability to problem solve, and an ability to develop an effective rapport with a variety of service users is essential. Working as part of a team in a collaborative way with a range of professionals is integral to the role.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;If you enjoy new and exciting opportunities and have the passion and energy to work in an environment that is committed to our staff and the people in our communities, we would welcome your application.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For an informal discussion or information about the role, please contact Claire Moase, Clinical Team Co-ordinator: 07825 316784&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
